HEADWORD: Embryotroph
<hw>Em"bry*o*troph`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'e`mbryon</grk> an embryo + <grk>trofh`</grk> nourishment.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The material from which an embryo is formed and
nourished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

